sequenceDiagram
    box Modernisation Platform
        participant Scheduler as Job Scheduler
        participant Matcher as Address Matching Job
        participant EM as Curated EM Address Data
        participant AB as AddressBase Athena Table
        participant Home as Home or Not Home Job
        participant GPS as Curated GPS Data
        participant S3 as S3 Artefact Store
    end

    box Ordnance Survey
        participant Places as OS Places API
        participant NGD as OS NGD Features API
    end

    box Cloud Platform
        participant DB as PostgreSQL/PostGIS
        participant API as EMDI API
        participant UX as EMDI UX
    end

    actor User as EMDI User

    Scheduler->>Matcher: Start scheduled address-matching run
    Matcher->>Matcher: Create run ID and load configuration
    Matcher->>EM: Read person IDs and messy addresses
    EM-->>Matcher: Return source address records

    Matcher->>Matcher: Clean addresses and extract postcodes
    Matcher->>AB: Read matching AddressBase candidates
    AB-->>Matcher: Return canonical addresses and UPRNs
    Matcher->>Matcher: Run exact and probabilistic matching

    loop Unique matched UPRNs not cached
        Matcher->>Places: Look up UPRN
        Places-->>Matcher: Return address record and TOID
        Matcher->>NGD: Retrieve building parts using TOID
        NGD-->>Matcher: Return building geometries
        Matcher->>Matcher: Merge building parts
    end

    Matcher->>S3: Write manifest, QA and intermediate artefacts
    Matcher->>DB: Upsert resolved addresses and home geometry
    Matcher-->>Scheduler: Matching run succeeds or fails

    Scheduler->>Home: Start scheduled home-status run
    Home->>DB: Read resolved address and home geometry
    Home->>GPS: Read person GPS positions
    GPS-->>Home: Return timestamped GPS observations

    Home->>Home: Calculate home/not-home intervals
    Home->>S3: Write manifest, QA and intermediate artefacts
    Home->>DB: Upsert home/not-home intervals
    Home-->>Scheduler: Home-status run succeeds or fails

    User->>UX: View person home-status information
    UX->>API: Request home/not-home intervals
    API->>DB: Query person, address and interval data
    DB-->>API: Return resolved address and home-status results
    API-->>UX: Return API response
    UX-->>User: Display home/not-home timeline